00:42:45,920 --> 00:42:47,320
Would you like something,
Peter?

744
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,834
No, thanks.

745
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:50,116
You should eat.

746
00:42:50,200 --> 00:42:51,236
Don't fight.
She'll win.

747
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:52,396
I will.

748
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:54,640
Okay, yes.

749
00:42:55,440 --> 00:42:56,635
You want
some coffee?

750
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:58,069
Yes, thanks.

751
00:42:58,560 --> 00:43:00,552
Do you have
any children?

752
00:43:02,080 --> 00:43:04,151
Two. A son and a daughter.

753
00:43:06,520 --> 00:43:07,510
Married?

754
00:43:08,320 --> 00:43:09,640
Divorced.

755
00:43:11,320 --> 00:43:12,993
What are their names,
your kids?

756
00:43:13,360 --> 00:43:17,320
There's Sarah. She's 11,
and Kevin is eight.

757
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:19,830
Do you have any pictures?

758
00:43:25,360 --> 00:43:27,670
Fuck!
I lost my phone...

759
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:30,751
Sorry, I should...
I gotta go...

760
00:43:30,840 --> 00:43:31,830
Peter, sit down.

761
00:43:31,960 --> 00:43:33,155
You're gonna
enjoy your sandwich,

762
00:43:33,240 --> 00:43:34,913
have some coffee
and stay the night.

763
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:40,275
Milk and sugar?

764
00:43:42,160 --> 00:43:43,310
Black.

765
00:43:44,720 --> 00:43:45,710
Some fresh towels.

766
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:48,153
There should be
soap and toothpaste,

767
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:50,033
everything you
need in the bathroom.

768
00:43:50,240 --> 00:43:52,152
Thank you so
much for doing this.

769
00:43:52,240 --> 00:43:53,879
It's nothing.
Sleep well.

770
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,356
What's going on, Peter?

771
00:44:09,080 --> 00:44:10,514
Talk to me.

772
00:44:14,520 --> 00:44:16,910
You think fresh towels
changes anything?

773
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:23,150
Changes what?

774
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:24,230
The shipyard.

775
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:31,075
If I was home and you pulled that
shit, I'd beat the fuck out of you.

776
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:35,518
I would crack your skull
on the pavement.

777
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:37,434
That's why I came
over here today.

778
00:44:37,520 --> 00:44:40,194
To fuck you up for
what you made me do.

779
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:42,509
I don't care how nice
you're being to me.

780
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:43,590
I don't give a shit.

781
00:44:44,080 --> 00:44:45,912
I'm gonna
wake up tomorrow,

782
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:49,114
and all these people,

783
00:44:55,120 --> 00:44:56,600
all my friends,

784
00:44:58,800 --> 00:44:59,995
are still fucked.

785
00:45:01,800 --> 00:45:03,154
And I'm still fucked.

786
00:45:06,520 --> 00:45:08,512
You fucked all of us.

787
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:12,190
But I'm gonna
get blamed for it.

788
00:45:13,520 --> 00:45:16,274
So, now I have to carry that
weight on my shoulders.

789
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:27,118
You fucked me, Frank.

790
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:31,151
I shouldn't have let you
do it, but I did...

791
00:45:50,440 --> 00:45:52,079
Are you done now?

792
00:45:55,320 --> 00:45:56,993
Get up.

793
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:02,030
No.

794
00:46:02,120 --> 00:46:04,794
I said get up.
And follow me.

795
00:46:05,640 --> 00:46:06,710
Now.

796
00:46:22,840 --> 00:46:23,830
Get in.

797
00:46:25,200 --> 00:46:27,510
Take off your clothes
and get in.

798
00:46:27,600 --> 00:46:28,590
Do it. Now.

799
00:46:49,320 --> 00:46:52,950
There was a DNC meeting earlier this week.
About the Governor's race.

800
00:46:53,400 --> 00:46:55,596
Your name came up as someone
we might want to run.

801
00:46:58,080 --> 00:46:59,958
Aspirin. Go ahead.

802
00:47:03,920 --> 00:47:06,310
Everyone in that room wanted
to cross you off the list.

803
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:08,073
I said no.
I stuck up for you.

804
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:10,073
I said, "Peter Russo,
he's got potential.

805
00:47:11,440 --> 00:47:13,955
"He's young, he's capable,
he's going places."

806
00:47:15,920 --> 00:47:18,230
I made them keep you
in contention.

807
00:47:18,480 --> 00:47:20,517
You're still
on that list.

808
00:47:21,960 --> 00:47:26,432
You show up at my house in the middle
of the night, drunk, to whine?

809
00:47:27,280 --> 00:47:29,272
To try to shift
the blame on me?

810
00:47:29,360 --> 00:47:32,751
Instead of taking responsibility
for yourself and your own actions?

811
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:35,915
Maybe they were right
in that meeting.

812
00:47:38,560 --> 00:47:39,960
Maybe you are worthless.

813
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:45,515
I'm the only person who
believes in you, Peter,

814
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:48,069
but maybe
that's one too many.

815
00:47:50,600 --> 00:47:52,796
The hot water will
open up your capillaries.

816
00:47:53,080 --> 00:47:55,595
The aspirin you just took
will make your blood thinner.

817
00:47:55,680 --> 00:47:57,592
It's up to you, Peter...

818
00:47:59,520 --> 00:48:01,876
And if you do decide to
take the coward's way out,

819
00:48:02,040 --> 00:48:05,795
cut along the tracks, not across them.
That's a rookie mistake.

820
00:48:26,560 --> 00:48:28,233
Morning.
Morning.

821
00:48:30,160 --> 00:48:31,480
You need a lift
to the Hill?

822
00:48:31,560 --> 00:48:33,074
I should go home
and change my clothes.

823
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:34,833
No, no,
we'll drop you.

824
00:48:35,720 --> 00:48:37,473
You want some coffee?

825
00:48:49,640 --> 00:48:50,630
Frank?

826
00:48:50,720 --> 00:48:51,710
One month.

827
00:48:53,400 --> 00:48:54,390
Hmm?

828
00:48:54,520 --> 00:48:56,352
One month sober.

829
00:49:02,440 --> 00:49:03,669
I can give you that.

830
00:49:05,080 --> 00:49:06,878
Not for me. For you.

831
00:49:12,200 --> 00:49:14,237
Has the seed
been planted?

832
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:17,075
Only Peter can
answer that question.

833
00:49:17,360 --> 00:49:18,714
He has a choice.

834
00:49:19,360 --> 00:49:20,635
Will he wither?

835
00:49:20,720 --> 00:49:22,632
Or will he thrive?

836
00:49:23,120 --> 00:49:24,554
Only time will tell.

